cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles north of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: moving north-to-north-northeast across the eastern Gulf of Mexico, then bending northeast toward Florida’s Big Bend/Apalachee Bay
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Apalachee Bay / Florida Big Bend coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: Englewood FL northward to Suwannee River FL (west-coast tropical-storm watch)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Keys, entire Florida west coast, Big Bend, then inland across north-central Florida and southeast U.S.
weather_observation.wind: Occasional gusts 20–30 mph possible late Thursday into Friday as outer bands sweep across northeast Florida.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected on Atlantic side of Jacksonville due to distant track.
weather_observation.rainfall: Generally 1–2 inches with locally higher totals possible in bands Friday.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous rip currents along northeast Florida beaches.
